<!-- §8 Problem this solves -->
<h2>Why Do Side Sleepers Hate Regular Bluetooth Earbuds at Night?</h2>
<p>Standard earbuds — even wireless ones — create pressure points when you roll onto your side. After 20–30 minutes on a pillow, most people yank them out. A sleep mask with embedded speakers solves this by keeping the audio hardware flush against your face, not inside your ear canal or wedged against the pillow.</p>
