<!-- §9 Supporting questions -->
<div class="supporting-questions">
  <h2>What Is the Boodlab Bluetooth Sleep Mask?</h2>
  <p>The Boodlab Bluetooth Sleep Mask is a 3D contoured blackout sleep mask with two ultra-thin speakers built directly into the side panels. It connects wirelessly via Bluetooth 5.0 and has onboard controls — volume up, volume down, play/pause — stitched into the front panel. The eye cups use a raised foam structure that creates complete light blockout without contacting your eyelids. It charges via USB and runs 8–10 hours per charge.</p>

  <h2>How Does It Compare to Sleeping with AirPods or Earbuds?</h2>
  <p>The main difference is comfort over time. AirPods and most in-ear earbuds are tolerable for the first 30 minutes but become painful when side sleeping because your ear gets compressed between the earbud and the pillow. The Boodlab's speakers sit outside the ear — they produce audio through the mask fabric rather than inside the ear canal — so there's nothing to press against. You trade a small amount of audio isolation for a full night of comfortable listening.</p>
  <p>Sound quality is noticeably lower than AirPods Pro — the Boodlab has no active noise cancellation and the "speakers" are thin transducers, not full drivers. For sleep podcasts, white noise, binaural beats, and sleep playlists it's perfectly adequate. For music you actually want to critically listen to, AirPods win. But if you're falling asleep to it, Boodlab is the better tool.</p>

