  <table class="tradeoffs-table">
    <thead><tr><th style="width:20%;">Tradeoff</th><th>The Reality</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Sound quality</td><td>It's not audiophile-grade. The flat transducers can't reproduce bass and sound thin at maximum volume. If you want quality music listening, use AirPods. For sleep, it's more than enough.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Nose bridge gap</td><td>In very bright rooms (blackout curtains open), a small sliver of light can enter at the nose bridge. The 3D structure works well but isn't a perfect seal for everyone depending on face shape.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Washing complexity</td><td>You have to remove the speaker module to wash the fabric. It's a 30-second process but adds friction compared to a standard mask you throw in the laundry.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Not noise-cancelling</td><td>The mask doesn't block external sound — it only plays audio. In noisy environments, you'll need the volume up, which reduces battery life.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>

