  <details open>
    <summary>Does the Boodlab Bluetooth Sleep Mask work for side sleepers?</summary>
    <p>Yes — it's specifically designed for side sleepers. The speakers are ultra-flat and flush with the mask surface, so there's no hard plastic pressing against your ear when you roll over. The 3D eye cups also lift away from your eyelids, keeping the blackout seal intact even when you're on your side.</p>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>How long does the battery last on the Boodlab sleep mask?</summary>
    <p>Battery life is 8–10 hours on a full charge at moderate volume, which covers a full night's sleep. Charging takes roughly 2 hours via USB. If you use it at higher volumes or pair via a phone that streams lossless audio, expect the lower end of that range.</p>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Can you use the Boodlab sleep mask without Bluetooth — just as a blackout mask?</summary>
    <p>Yes. You don't need to power it on to use it as a blackout mask. The 3D contoured foam blocks light effectively on its own. Just wear it unpowered if you only want darkness, no audio.</p>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Is the Boodlab sleep mask machine washable?</summary>
    <p>The fabric shell is removable and hand-washable. Remove the speaker unit before washing. Do not machine wash or submerge the electronics. Air dry completely before reassembling.</p>
